<h2>Sustainability Keyword Strategy</h2>
<p>Sustainability keywords follow different patterns than standard commercial or informational queries. Searchers use specific language that signals values, not just purchase intent.</p>
<h3>3 Types of Sustainability Keywords</h3>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Type</th>
<th>Example Keywords</th>
<th>Search Intent</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Problem-aware</td>
<td>"carbon footprint of fast fashion," "plastic pollution statistics"</td>
<td>Informational</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Solution-seeking</td>
<td>"sustainable packaging alternatives," "eco-friendly cleaning products"</td>
<td>Commercial</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Brand-comparing</td>
<td>"Patagonia vs North Face sustainability," "most sustainable [category]"</td>
<td>Transactional</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Most eco-brands target solution-seeking keywords only. That misses the top of the funnel. Problem-aware searchers represent the largest audience. They search for information about environmental issues before looking for product alternatives. Capturing them early builds brand awareness and <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">topical authority</a> in the sustainability space.</p>
<h3>How to Find Sustainability Keywords</h3>
<p><strong>Step 1: Audit existing sustainability content.</strong> Check which green keywords you already rank for in <a href="/blog/google-search-console-guide/">Google Search Console</a>. Many brands discover they have accidental rankings for sustainability terms.</p>
<p><strong>Step 2: Research competitor sustainability content.</strong> Identify which sustainability keywords competitors rank for. Check their blog topics, product descriptions, and landing pages for green messaging.</p>
<p><strong>Step 3: Target long-tail sustainability queries.</strong> Short keywords like "sustainable fashion" are hyper-competitive. Long-tail alternatives like "sustainable fashion brands under $50 for women" or "how to start a zero-waste wardrobe on a budget" have lower competition and higher conversion intent.</p>
<p><strong>Step 4: Map sustainability keywords to the buyer journey.</strong> Problem-aware keywords become blog posts. Solution-seeking keywords become product and category pages. Brand-comparing keywords become comparison content and FAQ pages.</p>
<h3>Keywords to Target vs Keywords to Avoid</h3>
