<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is sustainability SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Sustainability SEO covers 2 practices: optimizing your website to rank for green and sustainability keywords, and reducing your website's environmental footprint through green hosting, image optimization, and efficient code. Both practices align because faster, lighter websites rank better and produce less carbon.</p>
<p><strong>Does green hosting affect SEO rankings?</strong></p>
<p>Not directly as a confirmed ranking factor yet. But green hosting providers typically offer faster servers, which improves Core Web Vitals scores. Google has signaled that sustainability factors will increasingly influence search quality. The performance benefits create indirect ranking advantages.</p>
<p><strong>How do I avoid greenwashing in SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Make every environmental claim specific and measurable. Support claims with third-party certifications. Avoid vague terms without context. Publish what you are actually doing. Transparency builds trust with consumers, search algorithms, and AI systems.</p>
<p><strong>What sustainability keywords should I target?</strong></p>
<p>Target specific, substantiated terms. "Carbon-neutral certified shipping" outperforms "eco-friendly shipping." Use long-tail keywords matching your actual credentials. Map keywords to 3 types: problem-aware (informational), solution-seeking (commercial), and brand-comparing (transactional).</p>
<p><strong>Do AI search engines treat sustainability content differently?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. AI systems apply stricter criteria to sustainability topics because of greenwashing risk. Brands with verified certifications, consistent entity signals, and transparent reporting perform better. Unsubstantiated claims get deprioritized in AI-generated answers.</p>
<p><strong>How much CO2 does a website produce?</strong></p>
<p>A typical website generates 0.5 to 2 grams of CO2 per page view. At 10,000 monthly views, that is 5 to 20 kg of CO2 per month. Green hosting and performance optimization reduce these emissions by 80 to 90%.</p>
<h2>Green Rankings Start With Green Practices</h2>
<p>Sustainability SEO is where business growth and environmental responsibility align. The same optimizations that reduce your carbon footprint improve your search rankings. The same transparency that builds consumer trust satisfies AI search criteria.</p>
<p>The brands that commit to genuine sustainability credentials and strategic keyword targeting will capture the fastest-growing consumer segment. The ones relying on vague green messaging will lose both rankings and trust.</p>
